text: Acleris strigifera is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae. It is found in China, Japan and Russia. The wingspan is 19–22 mm. Adults are on wing from September, and after overwintering, to May.Check List of the Tribe Tortricini (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae) in Northeast china, with Two Newly Recorded Species from China ==References== Category:Moths described in 1931 strigifera Category:Moths of Asia
